My issue is probably related to the one OP has. On my Ubuntu 14.04.2 I had to explicitly put at minimum this two capabilities:

```python
capabilities = {
    evdev.ecodes.EV_REL: (evdev.ecodes.REL_X, evdev.ecodes.REL_Y),
    evdev.ecodes.EV_KEY: (evdev.ecodes.BTN_LEFT, evdev.ecodes.BTN_RIGHT)
    }
```
Omitting any of those will end up with a state where `py-evdev-uinput` is not registered in the `Virtual core pointer` list (as shown by the `xinput` command). 

