I'm trying to figure out the most efficient way to convert an array of ManagedObjectReference[]  to Managed Objects.   My code must get a list of VMs which are members of a DRS group.  I have code to get to the ClusterComputeResource , access the configurationEx.group and the ClusterVmGroup.   The ClusterVmGroup.getVm()  returns the array of morefIDs (e.g. ManagedObjectReference[] ).   I could use the following method to convert them one at a time as follows, but it is quite slow to call the server for each morefid   

    private VirtualMachine[] getVMsInDrsGroup(ServiceInstance si, ClusterVmGroup clusterVmGroup) {

        ManagedObjectReference[] morList = clusterVmGroup.getVm();

        VirtualMachine[] virtualMachine = new VirtualMachine[morList.length];

        for (int i = 0; i < morList.length; i++) {
            virtualMachine[i] = (VirtualMachine) MorUtil.createExactManagedObject(si.getServerConnection(), morList[i]);
        }
        return virtualMachine;
    }

Wondering if there is a better way to send the array of morefIDs to the server and get back the ManagedObjects.

