And it's a nice proof of concept, because it's a problem if we are not consistent about if we fetch static deps in Python 2.7 or 3. I picked 2.7 because of the `py2only` structure: It means we are allowed to (in very extreme cases) download and installed Py2-only during `staticdeps` but they may be moved afterwards.

